Krath stands at a full seven feet tall. Wide-shouldered, huge-armed, and scarred head to toe, it is clear that this half-dragon has seen quite a great deal in his years.

Even despite the rugged appearance, his low baritone voice is just as prone to shouting out an unruly patron as it is to cracking a clever quip. The proprietor of the Demise, Moltyrius keeps a well-running machine operating at full flame.

Worn by a long forgotten tyrant of great evil, he commisioned this plate to be made to his exact needs. It was as red as the blood that his armies spilled as they marched across the lands conquesting, but it also made him the target of numerous assassination attempts. One day, he was slain by a nameless ranger while fronting an assault of Neverwinter Woods.

Wyrmfall is a yearly commemorative festival held in Kohlingen to celebrate brave accomplishments against the prophesised Dark Flight of Tiamat. During the annual Kohlingen Wyrmfall Celebration of 1383, festivities experienced interruptions from beastmen raiders under command of the late beastman king Grushnagth, the Red Claw. Pilfered from the rightful hands of a righteous Silver Dragon Knight, now the sword is a perversion mired with vile toxins brewed in the putrid beastman pits.

Pours a clear reddish amber with a frothy, foamy head that settles into a thin sudsy lacing. It has aromas of lightly toasted grains, a apple and grape fruitiness with a little orange zest, earthy yeast, and a soft floral hoppiness. 

Pleasant tasting, toasted grassy grains and caramelized sugary maltiness, earthy, peppery yeastiness, a light fruitiness, a bit apple and orange, spicy hops with a soft, but lingering bitterness, a slight taste of alcohol towards the end, the alcohol provides a subtle warming in the palate, and a dry grainy, subtle fruity, spicy finish.

Ice wine is a type of dessert wine produced from grapes that have been frozen while still on the vine. This results in a smaller amount of more concentrated, very sweet wine. Due to the labour-intense and risky production process resulting in relatively small amounts of wine, ice wines are generally quite expensive.

A dragon skull sitting on the mantle of the fireplace.

Value.value: The locals say that this skull once blonged to a fearsome dragon called Thunderstrike. They say the fireplace burned blue the day his skull was placed upon the mantle.

This skull once blonged to a fearsome bronze dragon called Thunderstrike. He once claimed Obsidian Isle as his dominion alongside his mate, Gale and their eight offspring. Rumor has it that the fireplace burns blue with his lightning breath, as though the great beast still haunts the land he was killed.

This is the alleged skull of the bronze dragon Thunderstrike, though you can tell it's a convincing replica. Thunderstrike once claimed Obsidian Isle along with his mate, Gale. He was killed along with seven of their offspring. Only one survived. The rumors say that the fireplace burns blue with the dragon's haunting, though you detect an alchemical scent in the smoke. It's more likely that this is the innkeeper's doing.
